```javascript
function taBlur(itag) {
    var encodedVal = encodeURI(itag.value);
    window.location.href = "typeblurtext:" + encodedVal;
}
```

So when the input blurs, it sends the value. But the key issue is that when `displayCardAnswer()` is called, the code has:

```kotlin
if (!typeAnswer!!.useInputTag) {
    typeAnswer!!.input = answerField!!.text.toString()
}
```

